BlogPosts.paragraph1: Learn how to set up your first Vue project.
BlogPosts.paragraph2: Vue is a great framework to learn and I believe it is very friendly for beginners. As long as you have a general understanding of Javascript, HTML and CSS you can easily put together some great projects. Even if you are not too comfortable with those technologies just get started anyways. The only way to learn these tools is by creating projects on your own and honing your skills. Alright, so let's get started.
BlogPosts.paragraph3: First install node.js to get access to the node package manager. This allows access to all of the necessary packages.I will provide the link below but you basically follow the documentation. Select the correct operating system and follow the steps provided.
BlogPosts.paragraph4: Then check out the vue documentation to install vue cli. This allows us to create vue projects and manage many other features.

I will be using VS Code. There are also some great extensions you can use in VS code so let me know if you would be interested in learning more about those.
BlogPosts.paragraph7: So as you can see Vue is pretty easy to set up and get started! I think the ability to have the html css and javascript all in one component can really be nice for beginners. I hope you enjoyed the post!
